com.facebook.litho.sections

Class SectionTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.litho.sections.SectionTree

  • public class SectionTree
extends Object
    Represents a tree of Section and manages their lifecycle. SectionTree takes a root Section and generates the complete tree by recursively invoking OnCreateChildren. SectionTree is also responsible for regenerating the tree in response to state update events.

        Parameters:
        context - The SectionContext taht will be used to create the child Components
        target - The SectionTree.Target that will be responsible to apply the ChangeSet to the UI.

      • setRoot

        public void setRoot(Section section)
        Update the root Section. This will create the new Section tree and generate a ChangeSet to be applied to the UI. In response to this Target#applyNewChangeSet(int) ()} will be invoked once the ChangeSet has been calculated. The generation of the ChangeSet will happen synchronously in the thread calling this method.
        Parameters:
        section - The new root.

      • setRootAsync

        public void setRootAsync(Section section)
        Update the root Section. This will create the new Section tree and generate a ChangeSet to be applied to the UI. In response to this Target#applyNewChangeSet(int, String, Throwable) will be invoked once the ChangeSet has been calculated. The generation of the ChangeSet will happen asynchronously in this SectionTree ChangeSetThread.
        Parameters:
        section - The new root.

      • refresh

        public void refresh()
        Asks all the Section in the tree to refresh themselves. The refresh is by default a no-op. Sections that need a refresh behaviour should implement a method annotated with OnRefresh.
